goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different varieties of barley?
goals.visualization: grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: This visualization will allow us to compare the yield of different varieties of barley and identify which ones have higher yields.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield at each site?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the shape of the yield distribution at each site, allowing us to identify any differences in yield between sites.

goals.question: How does the yield vary between the two years in the dataset?
goals.visualization: side-by-side box plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will allow us to compare the yield distribution between the two years and identify any differences in central tendency and spread.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between the yield and the location where the barley was grown?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: This visualization will allow us to see if there is any correlation between the yield and the location where the barley was grown, which could help identify factors that affect yield.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['yield'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    ax.axhline(data['yield'].mean(), color='r', label=f'Mean: {data["yield"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['variety'] = data['variety'].astype('category')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['variety'])
    variety = data['variety'].unique()
    yield_data = []
    for v in variety:
        yield_data.append(data[data['variety'] == v]['yield'].mean())
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(variety, yield_data)
    ax.set_title('How does the yield vary across different varieties of barley?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Variety')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['yield'])
    sites = data['site'].unique()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for site in sites:
        ax.hist(data[data['site'] == site]['yield'], alpha=0.5, label=site)
    ax.set_xlabel('Yield')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield at each site?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data[data['year'] == 1931]['yield'], data[data['year'] == 1932]['yield']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['1931', '1932'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary between the two years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['site'] = data['site'].astype('category')
    data['yield'] = data['yield'].astype('float')
    chart = data.plot.scatter(x='site', y='yield', title='Is there a relationship between the yield and the location where the barley was grown?')
    chart.axhline(y=data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
